Details taken from:
http://www.visualab.org/index.php/using-google-rest-api-for-analytics

Before you generate a new refresh token, go to
https://code.google.com/apis/console, authorize the app for web
access, taking note of the client id, client secret and redirect uri

Hit this url:
https://accounts.google.com/o/oauth2/auth?
scope=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.googleapis.com%2Fauth%2Fanalytics&
redirect_uri=https://localhost/oauth2callback&
response_type=code&
client_id=992699852621-dajfjpdpbf4iod95gnd2175a7av5mkir.apps.googleusercontent.com&approval_prompt=force&access_type=offline

Where the value for redirect_uri and client_id are taken from the
equivalent values in the app console.

You should (eventually, after authorising a couple of links) end up at
a url like this one:

https://localhost/oauth2callback?code=4/8H9ZCWfpgQrqXf2bhcT9mgkxqA3x.orjUa-yuLJ4YOl05ti8ZT3b7cx2SeAI

Copy the code= querystring param, from (and includeing) the 4/ to (but
excluding) the .

=> 4/8H9ZCWfpgQrqXf2bhcT9mgkxqA3x

Then curl this url, inserting this in the code parameter:

curl  -H "Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded" -d
'code=4/8H9ZCWfpgQrqXf2bhcT9mgkxqA3x&client_id=992699852621-dajfjpdpbf4iod95gnd2175a7av5mkir.apps.googleusercontent.com&client_secret=uhSS518hG37x11DSDfB5R2V8&redirect_uri=https://localhost/oauth2callback&grant_type=authorization_code'
https://accounts.google.com/o/oauth2/token

This should give you a result like this:

result =>
{
  "access_token" : "ya29.AHES6ZRzsf7NFupz3jYzCfPwm9F2w2rYEWM8P64RTpYOaWDXDNL9Qw",
  "token_type" : "Bearer",
  "expires_in" : 3600,
  "refresh_token" : "1/vaXUBbpdTCtLiQcigXSd-QX2OeFRNYjOag84R2Z34Y8"
}

If you don't get a refresh token, you might need to deauthorise and
reauthorise the app

